Task 1: Understanding Authentication Coercion
Overview
Authentication coercion attacks force Windows systems to authenticate to attacker-controlled servers, enabling credential capture and relay attacks. Key protocols exploited:

MS-EFSRPC: Encrypted File System Remote Protocol (PetitPotam)
MS-RPRN: Print System Remote Protocol (PrinterBug)
NetNTLM: Challenge-response authentication protocol
